TASK 1: Depth First Search (DFS) Trace
========================================

Graph Adjacency Lists:
A: C B D
B: A C E G
C: A B D
D: C A
E: G F B
F: G E
G: F B

Source Node: A

DFS Trace (following Sedgewick & Wayne, page 537):
--------------------------------------------------

Step-by-step execution:

Initial State:
- marked[] array: all false
- edgeTo[] array: all empty
- Start at vertex A

DFS(A):
  1. Mark A as visited
     marked: A=true
     Visit order: A
  
  2. Check adjacency list of A: [C, B, D]
     
  3. First adjacent vertex is C (not visited)
     Call DFS(C), set edgeTo[C] = A
     
     DFS(C):
       4. Mark C as visited
          marked: A=true, C=true
          Visit order: A, C
       
       5. Check adjacency list of C: [A, B, D]
       
       6. A is already visited, skip
       
       7. Next is B (not visited)
          Call DFS(B), set edgeTo[B] = C
          
          DFS(B):
            8. Mark B as visited
               marked: A=true, C=true, B=true
               Visit order: A, C, B
            
            9. Check adjacency list of B: [A, C, E, G]
            
            10. A is visited, skip
            11. C is visited, skip
            
            12. Next is E (not visited)
                Call DFS(E), set edgeTo[E] = B
                
                DFS(E):
                  13. Mark E as visited
                      marked: A=true, C=true, B=true, E=true
                      Visit order: A, C, B, E
                  
                  14. Check adjacency list of E: [G, F, B]
                  
                  15. First is G (not visited)
                      Call DFS(G), set edgeTo[G] = E
                      
                      DFS(G):
                        16. Mark G as visited
                            marked: A=true, C=true, B=true, E=true, G=true
                            Visit order: A, C, B, E, G
                        
                        17. Check adjacency list of G: [F, B]
                        
                        18. First is F (not visited)
                            Call DFS(F), set edgeTo[F] = G
                            
                            DFS(F):
                              19. Mark F as visited
                                  marked: A=true, C=true, B=true, E=true, G=true, F=true
                                  Visit order: A, C, B, E, G, F
                              
                              20. Check adjacency list of F: [G, E]
                              
                              21. G is visited, skip
                              22. E is visited, skip
                              23. Return from DFS(F)
                        
                        24. B is visited, skip
                        25. Return from DFS(G)
                  
                  26. F is now visited, skip
                  27. B is visited, skip
                  28. Return from DFS(E)
            
            29. G is now visited, skip
            30. Return from DFS(B)
       
       8. Next is D (not visited)
          Call DFS(D), set edgeTo[D] = C
          
          DFS(D):
            31. Mark D as visited
                marked: A=true, C=true, B=true, E=true, G=true, F=true, D=true
                Visit order: A, C, B, E, G, F, D
            
            32. Check adjacency list of D: [C, A]
            
            33. C is visited, skip
            34. A is visited, skip
            35. Return from DFS(D)
       
       36. Return from DFS(C)
  
  37. B is now visited, skip
  38. D is now visited, skip
  39. Return from DFS(A)

FINAL ANSWER:
=============
DFS Visit Order: A → C → B → E → G → F → D

Edge-To Tree (parent relationships):
- A: (source)
- C: from A
- B: from C
- E: from B
- G: from E
- F: from G
- D: from C



